        <tr><td>
<a class="key" href="../../usa"><div  data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="Shortcut to United States of America" class="key">USA</div></a><a class="key" href="../../usa"><div  data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="Shortcut to United States of America (USA)" class="key">US</div></a><a class="key" href="../../../phone/drsn"><div  data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="Shortcut to Defense Red Switch Network" class="key">DRSN</div></a><a class="key" href="../../../intel/nato"><div  data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="Shortcut to North Atlantic Treaty Organisation" class="key">NATO</div></a><a class="key" href="../index.htm"><div  data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="Shortcut to Raytheon" class="key">Raytheon</div></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;        <div style="height: 20px;"></div>
        <table width=100% border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0>
          <tr><td height=4><img src="../../../img/blank.gif" width=1 height=4></td></tr>
          <tr>
          <td align="left" valign="center">
          <font size="+1" face="Lucida Grande,Arial,Verdana,sans-serif" color=#F52E00>
          <b>IST-2</b>
          </font>
          </td>
          </tr>
          <tr><td colspan=2 height=1><img src=../../../img/blank.gif width=1 height=1></td></tr>
          <tr><td height=4><img src="../../../img/blank.gif" width=1 height=4></td></tr>
        </table>
        <table width=100% border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
          <tr>
          <td valign=top align=left>
          <font size="-1" face="Lucida Grande,Arial,Verdana,sans-serif" color=#555555>
<b>Integrated Services Telephone</b>
<font color=#F52E00>- wanted item</font>
<br />
<br />
<b>IST-2</b> is an integrated services desktop <a href="../../../phone"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: telephone">telephone</span></a>
for <a href="../../phone.htm"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: secure/non-secure conversations">secure/non-secure conversations</span></a>,
in&shy;tro&shy;duced around 2003 by <a href="../index.htm"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: Raytheon">Raytheon</span></a>
in St. Petersburg (Florida, <span class="short" aria-label="United States of America" data-balloon-pos="up"><a href="../../usa" class="short" >USA</a></span>)
and subsequently manu&shy;factu&shy;rerd by
<a href="../../../manuf/telecore"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: Telecore, Inc.">Telecore, Inc.</span></a> in Richardson (Texas, <span class="short" aria-label="United States of America" data-balloon-pos="up"><a href="../../usa" class="short" >USA</a></span>).
It is intended for use on the <span class="short" aria-label="United States of America (USA)" data-balloon-pos="up"><a href="../../usa" class="short" >US</a></span>
<a href="../../../phone/drsn"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: Defense Red Switch Network">Defense Red Switch Network</span></a> (<span class="short" aria-label="Defense Red Switch Network" data-balloon-pos="up"><a href="../../../phone/drsn" class="short" >DRSN</a></span>) <a href="#ref_1">[1]</a>
and is therefore also known as a <b>red phone</b>.
The IST-2 itself does not feature encryption/de&shy;cryption, but instead relies
on the bulk encryption features of the local <span class="short tooltip-red" data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="Private Automatic Branch Exchange">PABX</span>.
          </font>
          </td></tr>
        </table>
<br />        <table width=100% border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
          <tr>
          <td valign=top align=left>
          <font size="-1" face="Lucida Grande,Arial,Verdana,sans-serif" color=#555555>
The device has 50 software-defined but&shy;tons &ndash; in a 5 &#215; 10 layout &ndash;
for direct access to a central office line (CO) or a local subscriber.
To the left of this direct access field is a numeric dial pad with the
regu&shy;lar 12 buttons, plus an extra row of <font color=#F52E00>red</font> buttons for
precedence and priority override, similar to the red buttons on the
telephone sets of the old
<a href="../../../phone/autovon"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: AUTOVON/AUTOSEVOCOM networks">AUTOVON/AUTOSEVOCOM networks</span></a>.
<br />
<br />
The difference with the old <span class="short" aria-label="Automatic Secure Voice Communication" data-balloon-pos="up"><a href="../../../phone/autovon" class="short" >AUTOSEVOCOM</a></span> network
&ndash; which faced many problems and high cost &ndash;
is that communication over the twisted pair line
is digital rather than analogue (<span class="short tooltip-red" data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="Plain Old Teleohone System (analogue)">POTS</span>).
          </font></td>
          <td>&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
          <td align=center valign=top width=100>
          <table 
           border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" ><tr><td align="center" valign=top>
<a href="img/ist2_large.jpg">            <div style="position: relative;" data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="Raytheon IST-2 integrated services telephone">
<a href="img/ist2_large.jpg">            <div style="position: relative;" data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="Raytheon IST-2 integrated services telephone">
            <img src="img/ist2_small.jpg"
             style="
             max-width: 618px;
            "
             align="left"
             vspace="4"
             alt="Raytheon IST-2 integrated services telephone"
             border=0
             width=298 height=200
             />
            </div>
            </a>
            </td></tr><tr><td align=center>
          </td></tr></table>
          </td></tr>
        </table>
<br />        <table width=100% border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
          <tr>
          <td valign=top align=left>
          <font size="-1" face="Lucida Grande,Arial,Verdana,sans-serif" color=#555555>
The IST-2 is only suitable for connection to a <span class="short" aria-label="Defense Red Switch Network" data-balloon-pos="up"><a href="../../../phone/drsn" class="short" >DRSN</a></span> switch,
which allows its users to place secure as well as non-secure calls
directly, without installing encryption keys and/or using a
Crypto Ignition Key (CIK). In a <span class="short" aria-label="Defense Red Switch Network" data-balloon-pos="up"><a href="../../../phone/drsn" class="short" >DRSN</a></span> network, security is handled
by the local switch, rather than by the individual terminals,
which makes setting up a call or a conference much easier for the users.
<br />
<br />
The IST-2 was introduced around 2003 and replaces the its predecessor
&ndash; the Raytheon IST &ndash; and the older
MLP-1A made by Electrospace Systems, that had been in use since 1983.
The IST-2 was phased-out around April 2011 during the presidency of
Barack Obama. It was replaced by two separate phones:
an Avaya/Lucent 8520T for non-secure calls through the regular White House
switch, and a Cisco 7975G Unified IP Phone ()
for secure calls <a href="#ref_4">[4]</a>.
          </font>
          </td></tr>
        </table>
<br /><div style="position: relative;">        <div style="width: 100%; height: 2px; background: #FFBB00; margin-top: 2px; margin-bottom: 2px;"></div>
