          <td valign=top align=left>
          <font size="-1" face="Lucida Grande,Arial,Verdana,sans-serif" color=#555555>
The image on the right shows <span class="short" aria-label="United States of America (USA)" data-balloon-pos="up"><a href="../../usa" class="short" >US</a></span> President George W. Bush (2001-2009)
using the IST-2 on his desk in the Oval Room at the White House for a
conversation with British Prime Minister Gordon Brown on 7 October 2008.
<br />
<br />
Although the 50 speed-dial buttons of the IST-2 were usually
<a href="img/ist2_obama_cover.jpg"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: covered by a grey panel">covered by a grey panel</span></a>
when the press was in the room, it ocassionally slipped
the attention of the White House staff, revealing the
<a href="img/ist2_bush_large.jpg"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: direct contacts of George Bush">direct contacts of George Bush</span></a> <a href="#ref_2">[2]</a>.
<br />
<br /><font color="#E7E">&#10148;</font>&nbsp;<a href="https://electrospaces.net/2021/03/the-telephone-contacts-of-president.html" target="_blank">Full description by Peter Koop (off-site)</a>
<br />
<br />
          </font></td>
          <td>&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
          <td align=center valign=top width=100>
